cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR

The paper proposes a visualization tool for analyzing classifier performance over time and comparing different models. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and data visualization. 

- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing an interactive visualization tool for data scientists. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper deals with classifier performance and model selection. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is another possible category as the paper mentions a case study on instance selection strategies in active learning, which is a common problem in computer vision. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with machine learning algorithms and model selection. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with analyzing and comparing different models based on their performance characteristics.
